ership elections and confidence votes such as that faced by Boris Johnson over ‘partygate’.How did the Committee come together? How is it structured and how much power does it really wield? These are among the questions the book considers. Providing unprecedented insights into this long-standing institution, it is essential reading for anyone who cares about the integrity of our political system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aParliamentary practicezGreat Britain. 70(DE-588)4032187-30(DE-627)1044838730(DE-576)208995951aKonservativismus2gnd 70(DE-588)4246883-80(DE-627)1048091400(DE-576)210483172aMachtstruktur2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  a1922 Committee.  a1922 general election.  aBoris Johnson.  aConservative Party.  aConservative Private Members' Committee.  aConservative leadership election 2022.  aLiz Truss.  aMPs.  aRishi Sunak.  aSir Graham Brady.  aTories.  aWestminster.  abackbenchers.  amen in grey suits.1 aNorton, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152617331740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526173317423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526173317/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles